<emphasis box="[576,736,1138,1161]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">Mare nostrum</emphasis>
, Latin name for the Mediterranean Sea.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[313,1269,1073,1545]" box="[353,927,1170,1194]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">
<emphasis box="[353,494,1170,1194]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[779,827,1170,1194]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[313,1269,1073,1545]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">
<emphasis box="[353,460,1201,1225]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">Remarks.</emphasis>
The sole species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill and Bush" authorityYear="1897" box="[711,793,1201,1225]" class="Bivalvia" family="Nuculanidae" genus="Ledella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nuculanoida" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[711,793,1201,1225]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">Ledella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
so far known from the Mediterranean is 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jeffreys" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[313,480,1234,1257]" class="Bivalvia" family="Nuculanidae" genus="Ledella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nuculanoida" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="messanensis">
<emphasis box="[313,480,1234,1257]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">L. messanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a wide latitudinal distribution through the European Atlantic (
<bibRefCitation author="WAREN, A." box="[325,476,1265,1289]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" refId="ref7156" refString="WAREN, A., 1978, The taxonomy of some North Atlantic species referred to Ledella and Yoldiella (Bivalvia), Sarsia, 63, 213 - 119." type="book" year="1978">Warén, 1978</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="WAREN, A." box="[493,549,1265,1289]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" pagination="223 - 259" refId="ref7272" refString="WAREN, A., 1989, Taxonomic comments on some protobranch bivalves from the Northeastern Atlantic, Sarsia, 74, 223 - 259." type="journal article" year="1989">1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="ALLEN, J. A. &amp; HANNAH, F." box="[566,865,1265,1289]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" pagination="123 - 171" refId="ref5749" refString="ALLEN, J. A. and HANNAH, F., 1989, Studies on the deep-sea Protobranchia: the Subfamily Ledellinae (Nuculanidae), Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, Zoology Series, 55, 123 - 171." type="journal article" year="1989">Allen and Hannah, 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="SALAS, C." box="[882,1021,1265,1289]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" pagination="33 - 100" refId="ref6956" refString="SALAS, C., 1996, Marine bivalves from off the Southern Iberian Peninsula collected by the Balgim and Fauna 1 expeditions, Haliotis, 25, 33 - 100." type="journal article" year="1996">Salas, 1996</bibRefCitation>
). However, it differs markedly from the present species by being bigger (up to 
<emphasis box="[1008,1033,1298,1321]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">ca</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1045,1111,1296,1321]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
), much more solid, and with a longer and sharper rostrum. Also, the juveniles of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jeffreys" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[1102,1269,1330,1353]" class="Bivalvia" family="Nuculanidae" genus="Ledella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nuculanoida" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="messanensis">
<emphasis box="[1102,1269,1330,1353]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">L. messanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are somewhat pointed posteriorly and thick-shelled. A North Atlantic species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Smith, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[313,654,1392,1417]" class="Bivalvia" family="Nuculanidae" genus="Ledella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nuculanoida" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="confinis">
<emphasis box="[313,486,1393,1417]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">Ledella confinis</emphasis>
(Smith, 1885)
</taxonomicName>
, revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="WAREN, A." box="[790,951,1393,1417]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" refId="ref7156" refString="WAREN, A., 1978, The taxonomy of some North Atlantic species referred to Ledella and Yoldiella (Bivalvia), Sarsia, 63, 213 - 119." type="book" year="1978">Warén (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, may be somewhat reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName authority="La Perna, 2004" authorityName="La Perna" authorityYear="2004" box="[397,553,1425,1448]" class="Bivalvia" family="Nuculanidae" genus="Ledella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nuculanoida" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="marisnostri" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[397,553,1425,1448]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">L. marisnostri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[561,623,1425,1448]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but it is larger, more solid, with a more pointed rostrum and with a strongly oblique umbo.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[313,1269,1073,1545]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">
The present species seems close to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jeffreys" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[805,972,1489,1512]" class="Bivalvia" family="Nuculanidae" genus="Ledella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nuculanoida" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="messanensis">
<emphasis box="[805,972,1489,1512]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1053">L. messanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, although it is not particularly similar to any of the European species.
</paragraph>
